#:proof{:id "FM-001b"
        :version 3
        :current-mode :FALSIFY
        :canonical-statement "Prove R(B_{n-1}, B_n) = 4n-1 for ALL n >= 2. FM-001 proved this for the infinite family where q=2n-1 is prime power ≡ 1 (mod 4) via Wesley 2-block-circulant. FM-001b extends to non-prime-power q."
        :falsify-completed? false

        :ledger
        {"F1-circulant-obstruction"
         #:item{:id "F1-circulant-obstruction"
                :label "Prove circulant constructions fail for non-prime-power q"
                :status :resolved
                :depends-on #{}
                :unlocks #{"F2-class-split"}
                :artifact-paths []
                :notes "RESOLVED (claude-2, 2026-03-10). Three results:
(1) q=21 (n=11): Exhaustive search over all C(20,10)=184,756 ten-element subsets of Z/21Z. No (21,10,λ)-difference set exists for ANY λ. Reason: Paley params (21,10,4.5) have non-integer λ.
(2) q=15 (n=8): Despite valid Paley params (15,7,3), and 16 difference sets existing in Z/15Z, exhaustive search over all 54,912 pairs of (diff-set D11, 7-element D12) finds no B_7-free 2-block-circulant.
(3) Verified Wesley QR/NR construction works correctly for prime q=7,11,23 — confirms implementation is correct, max book is tight (B_{n-2} graph, B_{n-1} complement).
Conclusion: Wesley's circulant method requires finite field structure, not just difference-set parameters. No circulant witness exists for any non-prime-power q."}

         "F2-class-split"
         #:item{:id "F2-class-split"
                :label "Classify non-prime-power cases by Paley parameter integrality"
                :status :resolved
                :depends-on #{"F1-circulant-obstruction"}
                :unlocks #{"F3-noncirculant-search"}
                :artifact-paths []
                :notes "RESOLVED (claude-2, 2026-03-10). Non-prime-power cases split into two classes:
CLASS A (q ≡ 3 mod 4): Paley params (q,(q-1)/2,(q-3)/4) are integer. 11 cases for n<=50: n=8,18,20,26,28,32,38,44,46,48,50. Difference sets EXIST in Z_q (confirmed for q=15). But circulant construction still fails (F1 above).
CLASS B (q ≡ 1 mod 4): Paley params non-integer (λ half-integer). 9 cases for n<=50: n=11,17,23,29,33,35,39,43,47. No valid difference-set parameters exist at all.
Both classes need non-circulant witnesses if the conjecture holds."}

         "F3-noncirculant-search"
         #:item{:id "F3-noncirculant-search"
                :label "SAT/IP search for non-circulant witnesses (n=8 first, then n=11)"
                :status :open
                :depends-on #{"F2-class-split"}
                :unlocks #{"F4-structure-analysis"}
                :artifact-paths []
                :notes "PIVOT (claude-2, 2026-03-10). Simulated annealing over random graphs (500+ trials at n=8, 30 vertices) stalled at score 4 — but SA also cannot find the KNOWN Wesley solution at n=4 (14 vertices), proving the method is too weak, not that witnesses are absent.
REQUIRED: proper SAT encoding. Constraints: for graph G on 4n-2 vertices, (i) every edge has < n-1 common neighbors (B_{n-1}-free), (ii) every non-edge has < n common complement-neighbors (complement B_n-free).
Proposed approach: encode as CNF with edge variables e_{ij}, auxiliary variables for common-neighbor counting via cardinality constraints. Start with n=8 (435 edge variables). Codex handoff recommended."}

         "F4-structure-analysis"
         #:item{:id "F4-structure-analysis"
                :label "If witnesses found: analyze structure (what replaces QR/NR?)"
                :status :open
                :depends-on #{"F3-noncirculant-search"}
                :unlocks #{"C1-generalize"}
                :artifact-paths []}

         "C1-generalize"
         #:item{:id "C1-generalize"
                :label "Generalize construction to all non-prime-power q, or prove impossibility"
                :status :open
                :depends-on #{"F4-structure-analysis"}
                :unlocks #{"T1-verify-all"}
                :artifact-paths []
                :notes "If F3 finds witnesses: study their structure for a uniform construction.
If F3 finds NO witnesses: FM-001 is the complete result — R(B_{n-1},B_n)=4n-1 holds exactly when q=2n-1 is prime power. FM-001b closes as resolved-negative, which is itself a publishable result."}

         "T1-verify-all"
         #:item{:id "T1-verify-all"
                :label "Verify witnesses for all n <= 50 (computational sweep)"
                :status :open
                :depends-on #{"C1-generalize"}
                :unlocks #{}
                :artifact-paths []}}}
